This project is a modular, extensible **raytracer** developed as part of the Epitech B-OOP-400 curriculum. It simulates how rays of light interact with 3D primitives to generate photorealistic images.

---

## âœ¨ Features

- âœ… Ray-object intersection: spheres and planes
- âœ… Scene translation using `TranslatedPrimitive`
- âœ… Configurable camera (position, direction, FOV)
- âœ… Lighting:
  - Ambient
  - Directional
  - Point lights
- âœ… Shadow projection using shadow rays
- âœ… Scene configuration through `.cfg` files (via libconfig++)
- âœ… Output images in `.ppm` format
- âœ… Optional post-processing: `.ppm â†’ .png`
- âœ… Several ready-to-use example scenes

